<br>
I managed to get my fleshgrinder with a single group (pre pop) - warrior, 2 SKs, cleric, chanter and monk but this was made easy because we knew the mob was up and our puller was able to bring it out single after clearing a couple of roamers.<br>
<br>
I used it initially with a frosty offhand which seemed to be a decent combo - huge upgrade in damage from what I had been using previously. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sulvar>Sulvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 3:13:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4881.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Obtaining a Fleshgrinder</span><hr size=1> 4C camp at level 60 almost requires a monk to FD pull or an enchanter to mez.  When you are in the maze looking at 4c the adept spawns at the left corner.  What we usually do to break 4c is to set up in the maze right before the 4c and pull the 2 door guards and all the roamers on the side of the pyramid.  Once these all are clear we either FD split the corner or just rush the corner where the adept is.  You will sometimes get a roamer add from the left side but rushing the corner isnt too bad.<br>
<br>
The main problem in 4C is that there are just a ton of roaming  mobs and not really any safe place to camp.  The safest place to camp is probably on the back wall where the ramp up to the pyramid is.  There is only one roamer on this side.  The downside to camping there, though, is that you need a lot of damage to clear out 2 sides and 2 corners to pull the adept to the back before everything respawns. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=179608">Gartuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> &lt;Ex Tempore&gt;<br>
